import React, { useState } from "react"; export default function Login(props) { const [inputs, setInputs] = useState({ email: "", password: "", }); const { email, password } = inputs; const onChange = (e) => { setInputs({ ...inputs, [e.target.name]: e.target.value }); }; const onSubmitForm = async (e) => { e.preventDefault(); try { const body = { email, password }; const response = await fetch("http://localhost:5000/auth/login", { method: "POST", headers: { "Content-type": "application/json", }, body: JSON.stringify(body), }); const ParseRes = await response.json(); console.log(ParseRes); localStorage.setItem("token", ParseRes.token); props.setAuth(true); } catch (err) { console.log(err.message); } }; return (
